         <abstract id="aspace_cf3de7443e664fb52ebebe03a2e39628">The George Platt Lynes diaries consist of diaries and datebooks which record his activities and thoughts, starting with a journal of Lynes' first trip to Europe in 1925 and ending with entries in a pocket datebook just weeks before his death in 1955. Though his early and later years are well documented, there are no diaries for the years 1931-1941. Accompanying the diaries are a few odd pieces of personal memorabilia, including a notebook of dinners given during the early 1940s and printed versions of writings by Glenway Wescott form the early 1920s.</abstract>
         <origination label="creator">
            <persname identifier="http://id.loc.gov/authorities/names/n83044552"
                      rules="aacr"
                      source="naf">
               <part>Lynes, George Platt, 1907-1955</part>
            </persname>
         </origination>
    
      </did>
